11.9.24  9:30 pm   on a scale of 1-10 how much do you worry about relevancy

      my main concern with 'relevancy' is to make sure that both items were mentioned. "is _____ relevant to _____ ?" As long as you mention what fills in those 2 blanks, then we can evaluate the answer. the freaky thing is when someone only mentions one thing and then asks if that 1 thing is relevant. (without saying 'to what')

11.9.24  8:46 pm   Is saying that you'd prefer to make a new song to be your favorite your favorite way of answering the 'what is your favorite song' questions, or would you prefer to make a new answer to be your favorite way of answering the 'what is your favorite song' question?

      that's usually not my answer to 'what is your favorite song'. i wouldn't be so quick to give the idea that my favorite song should always be one of my own. however, that is a good motivator to songwrite, so i sometimes hint at the feeling that i 'might' have to make my own just in case. the answer you're thinking of, "i would prefer to make a new one to be my favorite" is for a different question, when asked specifically about my own songs
